Tension is still high along the Kenya-Ethiopia border in Sololo, Marsabit after suspected militiamen attacked security officers who had arrested one of their members. According to witnesses, the suspect, believed to be a member of the Oromo Liberation Front, had been arrested at a police barrier along the Marsabit-Moyale highway on Wednesday afternoon and was being transported from Sololo to Moyale. ALSO READ:

Shock as students assault 'non-local' teachers The incident led to security officers aborting the mission and returning the suspect to Sololo Police Station where they sought help from the nearby GSU and AP camps.